{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And they were kept there in a special-- a special confinement area was constructed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And all were examined then by Allied examiners to determine which ones were responsible for vaarious things.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Most are them were turned loose.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But those that we could identify were tried and charged and-- and executed as a result of the Nuremberg Trials.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But I was always intrigued by all these stories on what-- what happened at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So in 1988, through a friend, I arranged for an interview for a German SS captain in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And my wife and I and another couple, the four of us, went to Germany and we met this SS officer in Trier, Germany.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "He could speak pretty good English.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was asked then to see if he was any way repentant, and he was very straightforward.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- but I could tell from our several hours we spent together in a little lodge up in the mountains out of Trier that he wasn't a damn bit repentant.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHING] It was apparent to me that the only thing he was sorry about was that they got beat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was an interesting experience, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have received-- I have received some letters from some SS officers since who participated in various battles that we were in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In any event, not many of the SS people were repentant about anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a special group of people and they were tough soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were fanatical.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But I don't think many people realize that we rounded them all up and incarcerated them and grilled them all.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And practically all of them are turned loose eventually, but they were kept prisoners for some period of time there right out-- near Dachau.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
